<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/34392099-stephen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1409235068i/34392099._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/34392099-stephen">Stephen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">According to Beidler and Barton Reader&apos;s Guide to the Novels of Louise Erdrich, the main action begins in or around 1919 on the un-named reservation a<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">According to Beidler and Barton Reader's Guide to the Novels of Louise Erdrich, the main action begins in or around 1919 on the un-named reservation and ends back on the reservation around 1933. Minneapolis is the setting in the interval . A back story begins, says the Guide, around 1870, when Anaquot (AKA Four Souls) survives what seems a fatal illness thanks to her mother's healing powers. Anaquot when she grows up will be the mother of Fleur Pillager<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
