    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_406535268" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/406535268" />
    <a title="Jennifer (aka EM)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1393336-jennifer-aka-em"><img alt="Jennifer (aka EM)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1510513814p2/1393336.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/406535268?book_show_action=true">Sep 03, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer (aka EM)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer (aka EM)" href="/user/show/1393336-jennifer-aka-em">Jennifer (aka EM)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer406535268" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3569349321604982028">This is a story of revenge. Anger and bitterness tempered by love. Turned into love. Unlikely love. Hilarious love. A mother&apos;s love. Spirit love. When everything fails, when everything is lost there is still love. <br/><br/>Only Erdrich writes this way...putting slapstick side by side with mysticism. Describing earthy vulgarities and cruelties in poetry. <br/><br/>The last couple of pages are filled with lyricism summarizing individual and cultural loss so perfectly, with such pain and grace. <br/><br/>Long live Louise Erdri</span>
  <span id="freeText3569349321604982028" style="display:none">This is a story of revenge. Anger and bitterness tempered by love. Turned into love. Unlikely love. Hilarious love. A mother's love. Spirit love. When everything fails, when everything is lost there is still love. <br /><br />Only Erdrich writes this way...putting slapstick side by side with mysticism. Describing earthy vulgarities and cruelties in poetry. <br /><br />The last couple of pages are filled with lyricism summarizing individual and cultural loss so perfectly, with such pain and grace. <br /><br />Long live Louise Erdrich. What a vision, what voices. Astounding. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3569349321604982028" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


