<span id="freeTextContainer6694719688658155629">I really enjoyed this book from the Erdrich Medicine Readalong happening in Instagram, and look forward to the discussion. We get to see Fleur going off to try to get her land back (often through the point of view of her husband&apos;s sister) and get a much deeper look inside the relationship between Nanapush and Margaret, which I loved so much. I may have liked this even better than <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/78887.Tracks' title='Tracks by Louise Erdrich' rel='nofollow noopener'>Tracks</a><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText6694719688658155629" style="display:none">I really enjoyed this book from the Erdrich Medicine Readalong happening in Instagram, and look forward to the discussion. We get to see Fleur going off to try to get her land back (often through the point of view of her husband's sister) and get a much deeper look inside the relationship between Nanapush and Margaret, which I loved so much. I may have liked this even better than <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/78887.Tracks" title="Tracks by Louise Erdrich" rel="nofollow noopener">Tracks</a><br /></span>
