<div id="review_1824342020" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1824342020" />
    <a title="Stephen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34392099-stephen"><img alt="Stephen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1409235068p2/34392099.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1824342020?book_show_action=true">Nov 28, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephen" href="/user/show/34392099-stephen">Stephen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1824342020" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1510717497088784362">Not my favorite of her marvelous books but the one I&apos;ve most recently read after a jag of LaRose, The Roundhouse and Plague of Doves. Fantastic and fantastical opening with a healing that leads to a revenge trek. A second narrative, about Nanapush and his machinations I did not like so much. He was just too kooky. I need to read Tracks now. </span>
  <span id="freeText1510717497088784362" style="display:none">Not my favorite of her marvelous books but the one I've most recently read after a jag of LaRose, The Roundhouse and Plague of Doves. Fantastic and fantastical opening with a healing that leads to a revenge trek. A second narrative, about Nanapush and his machinations I did not like so much. He was just too kooky. I need to read Tracks now. </span>
